January 30, 2007 06:03Chinanews, January 30 People's Daily reports that reporters learned from the Ministry of Commerce that ever since Chinese State President Hu Jintao announced eight Chinese economic and trade policies and initiatives for Africa for the next three years at the Beijing Summit of the China-Africa Cooperation Forum, relevant departments have been attaching great importance to follow-up implementation work of the Africa initiatives. The Ministry of Commerce sent five working groups to Africa by the end of 2006 to coordinate. At present, the various types of work are being orderly carried out.It has been reported that China will further expand the scope of its aid to Africa.In the next three years, China will double the scale of grants and interest-free loans to aid African countries and will strive to increase the proportion of grants to aid and build more social, cultural, and public welfare projects so as to truly benefit African countries and their peoples.In the next three years, China will provide Africa three billion US dollars in preferential loans with no political conditions attached.To support the work of the African Union, China will build for free a modern international conference center for the African Union, which will be relatively large-scale, fully functional, and able to satisfy international conference requirements.For all heavily indebted poor countries and the least developed countries in Africa that have diplomatic relations with China, debts owed to China in the form of interest-free government loans that matured by the end of 2005 will be canceled.Relevant Chinese departments have done a comprehensive sorting and verification of the debts concerned and will cancel 168 debts in the form of interest-free loans that matured by the end of 2005, which were owed to China by 33 heavily indebted poor countries and least developed countries in Africa that have diplomatic relations with China.The debt waiver agreement with debtor countries is planned to be executed before the end of 2007.In the next three years, China will enhance cooperation with African countries in human resource development, agriculture, medicine, social development, and education, among other areas.At present, rather detailed implementation plans have been developed by category, and relevant work has begun. Important progress has been made in some matters.(Gong Wen)